# A2A, MCP, and Azure Foundry — Check Docs First

When making changes to code that involves **A2A** (agent-to-agent), **MCP** (Model Context Protocol), or **Azure Foundry** (including any LLM calls), check the relevant documentation first so changes stay up to date.

**All LLM calls in this project go through Azure Foundry.** Keep usage aligned with the current SDK and APIs.

## When to check

- Editing `src/a2a/`, `src/mcp/`, or `src/llm/`
- Adding or changing agent message flows (A2A)
- Adding or changing MCP tools, client, or server
- Adding or changing LLM usage (chat, completions, models, API version)

## Where to check

| Area | What to check |
| --- | --- |
| **Azure Foundry / AI Projects** | [Azure AI Projects Python](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/python/api/overview/azure/ai-projects-readme), [Azure AI Foundry](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/azure/ai-foundry/). Confirm `AIProjectClient`, `get_openai_client()`, API version, and env vars (`AZURE_AI_*`). |
| **MCP** | [MCP Python SDK](https://modelcontextprotocol.github.io/python-sdk/), [MCP docs](https://modelcontextprotocol.io/docs/sdk). Confirm `ClientSession`, transports (stdio, Streamable HTTP), and `FastMCP` server usage. |
| **A2A** | Project design in `projectOverview.md` and `.cursor/rules/architecture-and-scope.mdc`. Our A2A is custom (`AgentBus`, `AgentMessage`/`AgentResponse`). |

## Before you change code

1. **Search or skim** the doc set above for the API or pattern you’re touching.
2. **Confirm** package names, method signatures, and env/config (e.g. `AZURE_AI_API_VERSION`).
3. **Prefer** the documented API over assumptions or old snippets.

This keeps A2A, MCP, and Foundry usage correct and up to date.
